entries.femaleVariant: That America's long-gone and forgotten. You might as well have started with "Once upon a time."
That's just it. It doesn't matter where we go – we're strangers in our own land. Every state is practically its own country.
It wasn't any different back then. Unity is a state of mind, Teddy. An imagined community. At least here, now, you know where you stand.
Look at it this way. Life can't disappoint if you don't have expectations, illusions. Maybe that's exactly what freedom is, brother.
Hi, fellas.
Isn't this...?
In theory. We fitted an afterburner and a multi-RPG launcher up top.
So, goin' for quick and agile now?
You'll take the wheel with Panam riding shotgun.
How about we take it for a ride now?
Since tomorrow's the big day already, how about we take her for a spin now? Wanna get a feel for her over the terrain.
Lo and behold.
We heard we're gearing up for a minor war.
Afterburner – what're we talkin'?
What's the firepower up top?
Afterburner – standard nitro or military-grade?
Firepower up top – what is it?
Sure thing. Maybe after sundown, though. We still have a few loose screws to tighten.
Standard couldn't move this baby an inch.
A rapid-fire, seventy millimeter multiple rocket launcher coupled with an onboard MMI you can sync to via personal link.
Where'd you get all this stuff?
Teddy salvaged it from a scrapyard. The launcher itself was fine, the problem was no ammunition.
As luck would have it, Dakota procured some. Don't ask me how.
So, nitrous oxide injection into military hardware?
So hardware's military. But how the hell'd you cram all that into a panzer?
When we unleash this beast tomorrow, you'll see.
Fellas.
Hey... Right now? OK.
Saul needs me.
More like a suicide mission.
Finish it up here, all right?
That's putting it mildly.
Will you quit being such a sourpuss? We'll have her ready in time.
If that's freedom, why do I feel like I can't breathe, like sombody's gripped my throat and won't let go?
Like I said, Teddy. It's a state of mind. Or, you know, the air.
Heard Raffens do the same thing with their armored pickups 'fore goin' after convoys. 'Cept it isn't exactly stable.
entries.maleVariant: Heard Raffens do the same thing with their armored pickups 'fore goin' after convoys. Except it isn't exactly stable.

entries.femaleVariant: You'd think you plain couldn't jazz up a panzer that way, huh?
Oh, small beans compared to the tricks we pulled with Scorpion during the war.
Preppin' comin' along?
Prep coming along all right?
You call this prep? I'd call it a damn improvisation, but that's just me.
Can it, Bobby.
Come find us after.
Will do.
We also scooped out about sixty percent of its total mass. Beautiful, isn't she?
You think you know all you need to? If not, fire away.
